data.text:
Glen Eden, Waitakere City

Glen Eden is a suburb which lies within the Territorial Authority of Auckland, one of 269 residential suburbs which form the wider region. Glen Eden is the 13rd largest suburb of Auckland in terms of the total number of residential housing stock. Glen Eden provides a range of housing stock, with the earliest residential housing recorded in the area constructed between 1890 - 1899. The majority of the residential housing stock in the locality was constructed between 1970 - 1979. Residential housing stock in Glen Eden is made up of approximately 94% residential housing and 5% residential investment housing properties.
